---
surface: graph-subgraph-types
bead: bd-rnfh
schema: ee.closure_surface_golden.v1
source: src/graph/mod.rs
assertion: typed graph snapshots partition memory-substrate metadata into deterministic graph families
graph_types:
  - MemoryLinks
  - CausalEvidence
  - RevisionDAG
  - RuleProvenance
  - ContradictionSubgraph
contracts:
  - GraphSnapshotType includes the five operational graph families.
  - Each typed graph refresh persists graph_type-scoped snapshot rows.
  - Typed refreshes use graph_type-scoped advisory locks before durable source reads.
  - Content hashes are deterministic across repeated refreshes of unchanged source rows.
  - The public CLI accepts targeted refreshes for memory_links, causal, revision, rules, contradictions, and all.
  - The causal refresh E2E inspects the persisted graph_snapshots row after public CLI execution.
  - The rule provenance graph remains bipartite and distinguishes rule-side and memory-side nodes.
  - All typed graph snapshots remain derived assets rebuildable from FrankenSQLite source tables.
evidence:
  - build_causal_evidence_graph_from_table
  - build_revision_dag_from_logical_ids
  - build_rule_provenance_bipartite_from_tables
  - build_contradiction_subgraph_from_memory_links
  - typed_graph_snapshot_refresh_acquires_write_lock_before_source_read
  - typed_graph_snapshot_refresh_persists_stable_hashes_across_refreshes
  - graph_snapshot_refresh_causal_persists_stable_snapshot_row
verification:
  - RCH job 332: cargo test --lib typed_graph_snapshot_refresh_acquires_write_lock_before_source_read -- --nocapture
  - RCH job 333: cargo test --lib typed_graph_snapshot -- --nocapture
  - RCH job 334: cargo test --test graph_determinism graph_snapshot_refresh -- --nocapture
